The Health Minister for the  in Chile reported on Tuesday, 21 confirmed cases of the virus on Chilean Navy's Sergeant Aldea supply vessel that visited the base between November 27 and December 10. On Thursday the local health secretary reported one more case in , where some Air Force Base civilian personnel live.

The  said on Sunday, the 36 people infected included 26 army personnel. They said the 36 people were moved to , the south-most region in Chile in the South America continent, where they were being monitored by local health authorities.

With this outbreak, the Antarctic continent became the last continent to report cases of what the World Health Organization declared a  earlier this year.

